Splitting Dataset¶

In [27]:
# Splitting Train and Test Dataset

from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

sc = StandardScaler()

feature_names = [index for index, value in df.iteritems()]
feature_names.remove('HeartDisease')

x = df[feature_names]
y = df['HeartDisease']
x = x.values
y = y.values

x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=25)

x_test = sc.fit_transform(x_test)
x_train = sc.fit_transform(x_train)

MULTILAYER PERCEPTRON¶

In [36]:
mlp = MLPClassifier(hidden_layer_sizes=(11,), random_state=1, solver = 'sgd', 
                    learning_rate_init = 0.1, 
                    activation = "logistic", 
                    shuffle = True)

""" Home-made mini-batch learning
    -> not to be used in out-of-core setting!
"""
N_TRAIN_SAMPLES = x_train.shape[0]
N_EPOCHS = 200
N_BATCH = 100
N_CLASSES = np.unique(y_train)

scores_train = []
scores_test = []
error = []


epoch = 0
while epoch < N_EPOCHS:
    print('epoch: ', epoch)
    
    random_perm = np.random.permutation(x_train.shape[0])
    mini_batch_index = 0
    while True:
        
        indices = random_perm[mini_batch_index:mini_batch_index + N_BATCH]
        mlp.partial_fit(x_train[indices], y_train[indices], classes=N_CLASSES)
        mini_batch_index += N_BATCH

        if mini_batch_index >= N_TRAIN_SAMPLES:
            break

    
    scores_train.append(mlp.score(x_train, y_train))
    scores_test.append(mlp.score(x_test, y_test))

    epoch += 1

 
plt.subplot(2, 1, 1)

plt.plot(scores_train, label = "Training Score")
plt.plot(scores_test, label = "Test Score")

zip_object = zip(scores_train, scores_test)
for scores_train, scores_test in zip_object:
  error.append(abs(scores_train-scores_test))

plt.plot(error, label = "Error")
plt.title('Learning Curve')
plt.xlabel('Epoch')
plt.ylabel('Error')
plt.legend(loc='best')
